  <title>Cogl.ColorMask</title>
  <p>Defines a bit mask of color channels. This can be used with
<link xref="Cogl.Pipeline.set_color_mask"/> for example to define which color
channels should be written to the current framebuffer when
drawing something.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>ColorMask.NONE</code></title>
  <p>None of the color channels are masked</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>ColorMask.RED</code></title>
  <p>Masks the red color channel</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>ColorMask.GREEN</code></title>
  <p>Masks the green color channel</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>ColorMask.BLUE</code></title>
  <p>Masks the blue color channel</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>ColorMask.ALPHA</code></title>
  <p>Masks the alpha color channel</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>ColorMask.ALL</code></title>
  <p>All of the color channels are masked</p>
</item>
